	(text "ok so im thinking i want to make a standard like isolated interface\nso i dont have to think about grounding, and so any like future boards\ncan be daisychained without any thought, also so i can kill power line noise\n\nalso to save board space and save from nuking efficiency, need it to \nbe one module that goes 12-5V and then ideally can take up to 24v\n\nso ima do what guitar power supplies do to get rid of wall noise and make\ngalvanically isolated power\neasiest way is to just buy a dcdc module, but that's kind of expensive\n(like 4$ a module)\nso let's see if i can make one myself...\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 48.514 40.132 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "5e51a20d-15c0-4a7c-b9a7-b4b1bb6b861c")
	)
	(text "so we need a switcher module, a decent transformer, inductor, decent caps,\nand some way to bring feedback across galvanic boundary for the supply itself\nideally some sorta pgood system... what else"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 147.2605 31.6618 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "78bf217f-5476-4d96-ad4b-7b7159317c29")
	)
	(text "DCDC brick options:\nCRE1S1205SC: only 200mA, no 24V capabiltiy, really bad (8-10% load line regulation), 3$\nNXJ1S1205MC-R7: only 200mA, no 24V capability, 10-12% reg, $3.55\nROE-1205S: 200mA, no 24V, like 15% regulation, $3.6\n1769405241: 400mA, no 24v, 8-15% regulation, $5.64\nMER1S1205SC: 200mA, no 24V, 4.5-5% regulation, $6.11"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 146.812 58.42 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "e6e87fe8-be39-482a-a6dd-775d20f14492")
	)
	(text "budget out half an amp @ 5V roughly for the whole board\nso 2.5W max"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 147.32 45.466 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "f1b0c2a1-9e42-423f-b177-e1caf20788a1")
	)
